results.name: Product_{p|n} F(p), where F(p) is the p-th Fibonacci number and where the product is over the distinct prime divisors of n.
link: Danny Rorabaugh, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..4000
formula: Multiplicative with a(p^e) = F(p). - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Jun 05 2006
mathematica: b[t_]:=Fibonacci[First[t]] a[n_]:=Apply[Times, Map[b, FactorInteger[n]]] (* Esa Peuha, Oct 26 2005 *)
program: (Sage) [1]+[prod([fibonacci(p) for p in prime_factors(n)]) for n in range(2,53)] # _Danny Rorabaugh_, Apr 03 2015
